<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 61-year-old retired grocery manager died Saturday after passing out in police 
custody, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Herbert Sewald of San Diego may have died of an accidental overdose of 
prescription medications and alcohol, a spokesman for the San Diego County 
coroner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
An autopsy is planned. 
</P>
<P>
Police are investigating, and they provided the following account: 
</P>
<P>
Just before 1 p.m. Saturday, police responsed to a call from a motor scooter 
shop on University Avenue, where they found Sewald passed out inside a display 
case. 
</P>
<P>
He was taken to the city detoxification center, which would not accept him 
because he appeared too debilitated. Officers took him to police headquarters 
to obtain approval to take him to County Jail, but Sewald stopped breathing 
while in the back seat of the police car. He was rushed to Physicians &amp; 
Surgeons Hospital, where he was declared dead. 
</P>
