<P>
Marina Klimova and Sergei Ponomarenko of the Soviet Union won the judges, but 
Isabelle and Paul Duchesnay of France won the crowd at the European Figure 
Skating Championships at Leningrad. 
</P>
<P>
To the overture from "My Fair Lady," world champions Klimova and Ponomarenko 
easily defended their European title in ice dancing. 
</P>
<P>
The Duchesnays, who delighted the crowd with a routine set to South American 
music, were third. Skating to a rising crescendo of Pan pipes, reed flutes and 
guitars, they depicted a struggle for freedom in South America. The program 
ended with Isabelle perched perilously on her brother's knee as he was bending 
backward. 
</P>
