<TEXT>
<P>
Sacramento King owner Gregg Lukenbill has admitted he helped raise money to 
defeat a new baseball stadium in San Francisco for the Giants, according to a 
published report. 
</P>
<P>
Lukenbill, who wants to bring pro football and baseball to Sacramento, told the 
Sacramento Bee he asked a Woodland-based steel manufacturer to donate money to 
the campaign against the ballpark. 
</P>
<P>
The subsequent $12,500 contribution was used for last-minute mailers in 
November that San Francisco Mayor Art Agnos called a "sleazy, underhanded 
effort" by Lukenbill to steal the baseball team and "loot" San Francisco in the 
aftermath of the earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
Lukenbill's campaign contribution is under investigation by the state Fair 
Political Practices Commission and the San Francisco district attorney's 
office. 
</P>
