<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: USD'S NORIEGA IS UPSET BY STANFORD FRESHMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The University of San Diego's Jose-Luis Noriega, the nation's second-ranked 
singles player, was upset by Stanford freshman Jonathon Stark, ranked sixth, 
6-3, 7-6 (7-4), in a match at Stanford Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Noriega's match was one of only three completed due to rain in Palo Alto. Thus 
the team match was called with No. 1 ranked Stanford ahead 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State's men's team improved to 3-0 with two victories, 8-1 over Weber 
State and 9-0 over UC San Diego. In the Weber State match, the Aztecs' No. 1 
player Tole Marinkovic defeated Dermot Sweeney, 7-5, 6-3, and No. 2 Dax 
Peterson beat Bob Rosene, 6-4, 6-2. Playing No. 1 against UCSD, SDSU's Hunter 
Galloway defeated Francois Monnar, 6-1, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State blew a 6-3 lead and eventually lost to Cal Poly Pamona in 10 
innings, 7-6. Scott Dennison went two-for-four with an RBI for SDSU (1-1). 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
USIU defeated Rice, 9-0, in a nonleague match at USIU. The Gulls got victories 
from Giovanna Carotenuta at No. 1 singles and Andrea Ritezc and Sarit Shalev at 
No. 1 doubles. 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State (2-1) lost to visiting USC, 6-3, in a Big West Conference 
match. Michelle Apra (No. 2 singles) and Paige Hammond (No. 6) were the Aztecs 
only singles winners. 
</P>
<P>
SWIMMING 
</P>
<P>
In a triangular swim meet at the University of San Diego, UC San Diego beat 
USD, 87-26 and USC defeated USD and UCSD. UCSD's Katherine Caprilez won the 
400-yard individual medley and the 100-yard backstroke. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Julie Evans scored 22 points and grabbed five rebounds in San Diego State's 
91-51 loss at UNLV. 
</P>
<P>
The Aztecs dropped to (4-18, 3-8) and UNLV improved to (18-1, 11-0). 
</P>
<P>
Paula Mascari scored 16 points and three other USD players had 10 each as the 
Toreros beat Gonzaga, 62-54. 
</P>
<P>
Candida Echeverria, Lynda Jones and Christi English each scored 10 points for 
the University of San Diego (13-8, 3-5). Echeverria also had seven assists and 
five rebounds. Freshman center Chris Enger blocked 10 shots for USD. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
U.S. International split a double-header with visiting UCLA, the defending NCAA 
champion. UCLA won the first game, 2-0, and USIU won the second game, 3-2. 
After managing only one hit in the first game, USIU got two hits from center 
fielder Amy Geldbach in game two and scored three runs in the second inning. 
</P>
<P>
UCLA (1-1) loaded the bases with no outs in the top of the seventh, but Gelbach 
caught a fly ball and threw out a runner at the plate. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Point Loma Nazarene lost to Grand Canyon University, 60-52, in a nonconference 
game at Golden Gymnasium. 
</P>
<P>
Ron Hubbard scored 18 points to lead Point Loma (6-17), which trailed 33-29 at 
halftime. Eric Taylor led Grand Canyon (17-8) with 12 points. 
</P>
