HOME IMPROVEMENT; 
</P>
<P>
CONVERTING 2 BEDROOMS INTO MASTER SUITE PAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Converting two existing bedrooms into a master suite can make an existing home 
competitive with new construction, according to Remodeling Magazine. 
</P>
<P>
The expected pay back from such a remodeling job averages 79% nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
Experts advise undertaking the project only if the house will still have at 
least three bedrooms. 
</P>
<P>
An additional bathroom considerably increases the marketability of a home with 
one or 1 1/2 baths, according to Remodeling Magazine. 
</P>
<P>
Use high-quality materials that are easy to clean. Use lots of mirrors and 
include ample storage. Skylights brighten interior bathrooms and help to make a 
small room look larger. 
</P>
</TEXT>
