ORANGE COUNTY BOMA HONORS BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Transamerica building, which has an unusual stepped facade, has been named 
"1989 Office Building of the Year" by the Orange County chapter, Building 
Owners &amp; Managers Assn. 
</P>
<P>
The 11-story, 219,678-square-foot building was designed by Gensler &amp; 
Associates, Architects, and was completed in 1985 at 18201 Von Karman Ave., in 
the $54-million Koll Center Irvine. 
