<HEADLINE>
<P>
REAL ESTATE CONFERENCE AT TWO SITES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some of California's top real estate experts will discuss today's real estate 
market at a program sponsored annually by the Real Estate Conference Group. 
</P>
<P>
The conference will take place Feb. 26 at the Regent Beverly Wilshire Hotel in 
Beverly Hills and March 1 at the Hyatt Regency Alicante in Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
The daylong program is designed to benefit persons interested in real estate, 
including real estate brokers; sales, leasing and management agents; mortgage 
brokers and bankers; developers, contractors, attorneys and CPAs. 
</P>
<P>
Keynote speaker for the program in Beverly Hills will be Ray A. Watt, chairman 
and chief executive officer of Watt Industries. 
</P>
<P>
In Garden Grove, the speaker will be William E. B. Siart, chairman, president 
and chief executive officer of First Interstate Bank of California. 
</P>
<P>
Each location features a separate keynote speaker, but the rest of the program 
is duplicated at each site. 
</P>
<P>
The new economic climate will be presented by Jack Kyser, chief economist for 
the Los Angeles Area Chamber of Commerce; Robert Charles Lesser, chairman of 
Robert Charles Lesser &amp; Co., and Neal A. Roberts, senior manager of the 
Roulac Group of Deloitte &amp; Touche. 
</P>
<P>
Special presentations will be made on the Resolution Trust Corp. by Peter F. 
McAndrews, partner, Cox, Castle &amp; Nicholson; asbestos and toxics by Joel S. 
Moskowitz, partner, Gibson, Dunn &amp; Crutcher, and Mark A. Pisano, executive 
director of the Southern California Assn. of Governments. Stan Ross, 
co-managing partner at Kenneth Leventhal &amp; Co. will discuss tax strategies. 
</P>
<P>
Panelists analyzing perspectives on investing are Richard Bobrow, western 
regional director, Ernst &amp; Young Real Estate Advisory Group; David A. 
Eisner, managing partner, Southern California Real Estate Group, Price 
Waterhouse, and Andrew S. Kane, director of real estate services, Arthur 
Andersen &amp; Co. 
</P>
<P>
Presentations on investment trends will be made by E. Olena Berg, executive 
vice president of Lowe Enterprises; James S. Carlson, senior vice president of 
Equitable Real Estate; Jim Gallagher, senior vice president of La Salle 
Partners; Stanley L. Iezman, chief operating officer of Smith Barney Birtcher 
Realty Advisors; Mont E. McMillen Jr., executive vice president of Haseko 
Corp., U.S.A., and Richard Pink, senior vice president of TCW Realty Advisors. 
</P>
<P>
Scheduled to speak on new development concepts are Jeffrey B. Allen, managing 
partner of Paragon Group; Harry Newman Jr., chairman of Newman Properties and 
Newman Properties Northwest, and Milton I. Swimmer, partner, J.H. Snyder Co. 
</P>
<P>
Panelists analyzing financing are Robert E. Hamaguchi, senior vice president of 
Security Pacific National Bank; George A. Smith, chairman, George Smith/Grubb 
&amp; Ellis Financial Services, and Carol S. Weiss, director of real estate 
finance for Prudential Mortgage Capital Co. 
</P>
<P>
International investing will be detailed by Robert Brasch, vice chairman of the 
World Trade Bank and president of Pacific Partners; Lowell C. Martindale, 
partner, O'Melveny &amp; Myers, and Jack R. Rodman, managing partner of Kenneth 
Leventhal &amp; Co. 
</P>
<P>
Marketing strategies will be presented by Raymond L. Garland, vice president of 
Coldwell Banker Commercial Real Estate Investment Banking Services; Harvey E. 
Green, vice president and managing director of Marcus &amp; Millichap, and 
Dennis Macheski, vice president and regional director of research for Grubb 
&amp; Ellis. 
</P>
<P>
The program is from 8:30 a.m. to 5 p.m. and includes lunch, refreshments, 
cocktail reception and the program material. Registration is $175 if paid by 
Feb. 20. After that date, the fee is $195. 
</P>
<P>
The program has been approved for nine hours of DRE credit and is available for 
CPA continuing education credit. 
</P>
<P>
Real Estate Conference Group, directed by Martin and Barbara Stolzoff, produces 
and develops real estate seminars throughout California. 
</P>
</TEXT>
