<P>
ATLANTIS CREW COMPLETES TEST FOR MILITARY MISSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KENNEDY SPACE CENTER, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Atlantis' five astronauts completed a countdown rehearsal inside the shuttle 
Saturday for their classified military mission later this month. 
</P>
<P>
As planned, the test ended five seconds before the clock reached zero to 
simulate an aborted liftoff in which the three main engines shut down after 
ignition. "Everything went according to plan," said NASA spokeswoman Lisa 
Malone. 
</P>
<P>
Sources close to the project said the crew will put a spy satellite into orbit. 
</P>
