<TEXT>
<P>
May I express my indignation? Allegedly Bill Kenkelen, West Coast correspondent 
for the liberal National Catholic Reporter said that Mahony is "a church 
political animal." 
</P>
<P>
Further: "He was liberal in the '60s, when it was profitable to be liberal. And 
now under this Pope, it's advantageous to be conservative." 
</P>
<P>
I do not know who Kenkelen is, but I am sure that he is a not-well-educated 
Catholic. He should know that there are basic doctrines in the Catholic faith 
that do not depend on who the Pope is. Another quotation, from Father Thomas 
Reese, that "bishops are not liberal Democrats -- they are coming out of a 
Christian perspective" is the right judgment in this question. 
</P>
<P>
STEPHEN J. FELSZEGHY, Los Angeles 
