<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA: DESIGN; 
</P>
<P>
STILL LIFES WITH BLOSSOMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARBARA THORNBURG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'I LEARNED ALL THE traditional ways of creating flower arrangements," Chris 
Slack says, "but I never wanted to do them like anyone else." No chance of 
that. 
</P>
<P>
Slack doesn't create flower arrangements but rather natural still-life 
sculptures, with a magnificent bloom or spray of orchids as the focal point. 
"The Package" is a giant banana leaf folded to resemble a large green pocket 
book. Inside is an orchid, or perhaps chocolate truffles or champagne. "The 
Flower Wall" seemingly holds a bloom afloat in midair. Roses in "The Bamboo 
Log" look as pretty dried as they do fresh. For those who want to learn how to 
create such untraditional arrangements, Slack also teaches classes. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Slack Flower Artist, 1346 N. Formosa Ave., Los Angeles, (213) 851-6961. 
BARBARA THORNBURG 
</P>
</TEXT>
