<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MOVIE CHART: FILMS NOW GOING INTO PRODUCTION: 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By David Pecchia 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Adios (tentative title) (Electric). Shooting in New Orleans. Nicolas Cage, 
Judge Reinhold and ex-model Erika Anderson star in this dramatic and erotic 
love triangle set in New Orleans. Cage plays a struggling artist and Reinhold a 
boyhood friend who both get tangled up in the passions of the beautiful 
Anderson. Executive producers Nicole Seguin and Staffan Ahrenberg. Producers 
William Blaylock and Eyal Rimmon. Director Sam Pillsbury. Screenwriter Mari 
Kornhauser. Also stars Joe Pantoliano, Viveca Lindfors and Aaron Neville. Fall 
release. 
</P>
<P>
Battle Gear (Concorde). Shooting in the Philippines. David Carradine and 
"Streets" villain Eb Lottimer star in this tale of a battalion and their 
special relationship with company leader Carradine as they go into the jungles 
of Vietnam. Producer Roger Corman. Director Cirio Santiago. Screenwriter David 
A. Thomas. Also stars Scott Utley, Don Barnes and David Anthony Smith. 
</P>
<P>
Eminent Domain (SVS/Arama). Shooting in Warsaw. A romantic thriller based on 
actual events, starring Donald Sutherland and Anne Archer as a high level 
communist official and his wife. Sutherland's a loyal member of the Polish 
Politburo whose security clearance is suddenly and inexplicably revoked so he 
and the wife use their love for each other to fend off the tyrannical 
government and avoid imprisonment. Producer Shimon Arama. Director John Irvin. 
Screenwriter Andrej Krakowski. Distributor SVS. 
</P>
<P>
The King of the Kickboxers (Seasonal). Shooting in Bangkok and Toronto. Lots of 
martial arts action as an undercover cop/kickboxing enthusiast goes to Thailand 
to break up a ring of illegal movie makers. Executive producer Ng See Yuen. 
Producer/screenwriter Keith W. Strandberg. Stars Loren Avedon. Summer release. 
</P>
<P>
Scissors (D.D.M.). Shooting in L.A. Sharon Stone and "The Stunt Man's" Steven 
Railsback star in this psychological thriller of a woman whose deep, dark past 
threatens to jeopardize her very existence. Producers Hal Polaire, Mel Pearl 
and Dan Levine. Director Frank De Felitta. Screenwriters De Felitta and the 
late Joyce Selznick. Also stars Vicki Frederick. David Pecchia 
</P>
