<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALLAN ULRICH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The occasion for this potpourri concert, the Met's spring 1988 visit to Japan, 
summoned superlative sonics in Tokyo's Bunka Kaikan and gleaming performances 
from all participants. Domingo's attempts to fill Don Giovanni's baritonal 
shoes remain as bewildering as ever, but he and Battle infuse duets from "La 
Traviata," "L'Elisir d'Amore," "The Merry Widow" and "Romeo et Juliette" with 
considerable poise and style. Levine's traversals of the overtures to "La Forza 
del Destino" and "L'Italiana in Algeri" are spit-and-polish affairs, and the 
audience reaction is understandably vociferous. ALLAN ULRICH 
