<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO LEADING LADIES OF THE SCREEN LEAVE BEHIND SWEET MEMORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At a 1947 forum at the Beverly Wilshire Hotel, a brash young friend asked me to 
keep his seat while he was off being brash. 
</P>
<P>
A woman, almost formless under layered sweaters, approached to ask me if the 
seat was taken. 
</P>
<P>
I replied, "Yes, I'm sorry," and I've been sorry ever since. Because when I 
looked at her face, I saw it was Ava Gardner. 
</P>
<P>
If I had allowed myself a quota of mistakes, turning down this glorious beauty 
surely would have used up my quota far into the future. 
</P>
<P>
MARK NICHOLS 
</P>
<P>
Beverly Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
