<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAPPLETHORPE IMAGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Really, Wilson, why all the fuss? 
</P>
<P>
Maybe it's because Mapplethorpe had an intense courage to photograph his world 
and present it to the public instead of leaving it in some crowded closet to be 
discovered after he was dead. 
</P>
<P>
I don't think it had anything to do with Jim Morrison, Andy Warhol or a 
6-year-old Almodovar film. I think Mapplethorpe was a genius, now a casualty 
who will be missed. 
</P>
<P>
RANDY LUJAN-PESQUEIRA 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
