<HEADLINE>
<P>
UC SANTA BARBARA ROUTS FRESNO STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gary Gray scored 18 points to lead UC Santa Barbara to a 78-57 Big West 
Conference basketball victory over Fresno State Saturday night at Goleta. 
</P>
<P>
Eric McArthur added 15 points and grabbed 20 rebounds for the Gauchos (14-5 
overall, 8-3 in the Big West.) 
</P>
<P>
Tod Bernard scored 15 points for Fresno State (8-11, 3-7). 
</P>
<P>
Santa Barbara led, 37-28, at the half, but the Bulldogs scored the first four 
points of the second half to make it 37-32 with 18:34 left. 
</P>
<P>
But Fresno State was held scoreless for the next 3:06 while the Gauchos scored 
17 points in a row. The Gauchos built their largest lead, 54-37, with 10:06 
left to play when Carrick DeHart scored on a layup. 
</P>
