<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ANTELOPE VALLEY WOMEN GAIN FIRST-PLACE TIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Antelope Valley lost an eight-point lead in the final eight minutes of 
regulation play but came back to take a 66-60 overtime victory over Desert in a 
women's Foothill Conference basketball game Saturday at Paraclete High. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley's Denese Prince sank a free throw with 35 seconds remaining to 
send the game into overtime. Sophomore forward Molly Jonnum (20 points and 13 
rebounds) scored six points in the overtime period. 
</P>
<P>
With the win, Antelope Valley (13-10, 8-1 in conference play) improved its 
hopes for a conference title, pulling even with Desert (17-6, 8-1) for first 
place in the Foothill standings. 
</P>
<P>
In other women's games: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge 69, CS Los Angeles 67 -- Dawn Broline hit a 16-foot jump 
shot with 15 seconds left to give Northridge a victory in the California 
Collegiate Athletic Assn. game at Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Cal State L. A. (7-14, 1-6) had three chances to tie the score but failed. 
Millie Junio missed the front end of a one-and-one opportunity with 14 seconds 
left, Sabrina Yap missed a jump shot with two seconds remaining, and Kristen 
McDonald's follow shot caromed off the rim at the buzzer. 
</P>
<P>
Julie Arlotto scored a game-high 17 points for Northridge (9-13, 6-1) and moved 
to fourth on the Lady Matadors' all-time career list with 932 points. 
</P>
<P>
Canyons 87, Cuesta 65 -- Tressie Millender and Kim Posey each scored 17 points 
to lead host Canyons (19-5, 7-2) in a Western State Conference game. Michelle 
Cabaldon scored 13 points and Dawn Coleman and Dee Dee Hinson each added 10 for 
Canyons. 
</P>
<P>
Point Loma Nazarene 82, Cal Lutheran 69 -- Brenda Lee scored 18 points and 
grabbed a game-high 19 rebounds in a losing effort in a National Assn. of 
Intercollegiate Athletics District 3 game at Cal Lutheran. Leslie Stevens 
scored 15 and Dani Elton added 11 for the Regals (13-7, 6-4 in District 3 
play). 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 68, Pierce 66 -- Debbie Rabin scored 23 points and Cindy Wiley added 
16 to pace the Raiders (16-8, 7-2) in a WSC game at Pierce. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Occidental 83, Claremont 75 -- Ethan Caldwell had 24 points and seven assists 
and Chris Anderson added 18 points and 12 rebounds for Occidental (8-13, 4-4). 
Everette Hill had 16 points and John Crawley added 12. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran 85, Dominican College 82 -- Jeff deLaveaga scored a game-high 36 
points and Mike Demeter hit the front end of a one-and-one with five seconds 
left to secure the NAIA District 3 win for host Cal Lutheran (5-16, 3-3). 
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
Mission 12, Pierce 2 -- The Free Spirit got nine hits, including home runs by 
Rudy Sanchez and Shawn Fontenot, to back the strong pitching of Nick 
Lymberopoulos in a game at Pierce. 
</P>
<P>
Brad McGahan added two hits and three runs batted in for Mission (2-0). 
</P>
<P>
The Master's 7, Cal State L.A. 3 -- Mark MacArthur was three for four and Tony 
Jaime added two hits and two runs for The Master's (1-1) in a nonleague game at 
Cal State L.A. (0-3). Craig Johnson was two for five with two RBIs for The 
Master's. 
</P>
