<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL NEWS: LIONS PLAN SCHOLARSHIPS FOR FLAG SPEECH WINNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Walnut students interested in entering the annual California-Nevada Lions 
International Student Speakers Contest must submit applications by Feb. 15. 
</P>
<P>
Students will vie for up to $12,000 in scholarships by giving speeches on this 
year's subject: "What the American Flag Means to Me." 
</P>
<P>
The student speaker contest, hosted by the Walnut Lions Club, will begin at the 
Walnut City Community Center Feb. 22 at 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Students from Walnut, Del Paso and Nogales high schools should contact Eric 
Harmon at (714) 598-5065 or Ray Watson at (714) 598-2091. Other high school 
students should contact Lions District Student Speaker Chairman Rod Wallace at 
(714) 535-0645 or (714) 738-1496. 
</P>
</TEXT>
