<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESERVING YOSEMITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How ironic! We live in a time of the business philosophy "bottom-line 
mentality." 
</P>
<P>
Give only if there is a large profit. MCA has too long applied this principle 
to our national wonder, Yosemite. Hey, that's a public park. Get the rascals 
out. Create a nonprofit organization and apply the profits to saving and 
preserving the park. 
</P>
<P>
Always amazing how the private sector exploits the public one. Another example 
of using and abusing without a care. I am also referring to the public bailout 
of the Lincoln Savings &amp; Loan mess. Where are those enlightened folks who 
realize there is more to this life than money, profits and greediness? 
</P>
<P>
BYRON KANODE 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
</P>
