<P>
CHAPMAN FALLS VICTIM TO COLD SPELLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORANGE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Dominguez Hills pulled away in the second half to defeat Chapman, 
56-47, in a California Collegiate Athletic Assn. men's basketball game Saturday 
night in Hutton Center. 
</P>
<P>
The loss was the fifth in six games for Chapman, which dropped to 10-11 and 2-6 
in the CCAA. 
</P>
<P>
Dominguez Hills is 8-13, 4-4. 
</P>
<P>
Frantz Reyes made a jump shot to give Chapman a 22-21 lead one minute 10 
seconds into the second half, but the Panthers failed to score a point over the 
next 7:40. Chris Martin made a three-pointer to bring Chapman within five 
points at 30-25, but the Panthers then went another five minutes without 
scoring. 
</P>
<P>
Reyes made two free throws with 5:52 remaining, but Chapman was behind, 43-28. 
The Panthers made a mini-run in the game's final minutes, with Martin and Kevin 
Stafford making some three-pointers. Martin, who led Chapman with 16 points, 
had four three-pointers in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Vincent Washington scored 16 for Dominguez Hills, and Brian Johnson held 
Chapman's leading scorer, Roger Middleton, to 11 points -- only one of which 
came in the second half. MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</TEXT>
