<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SUBSTITUTE FILLS IN NICELY, SPARKS RANCHO SANTIAGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MISSION VIEJO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rancho Santiago College's Mike Hunter made four consecutive key plays late in 
the second half to help the Dons to an 83-75 victory over Saddleback Saturday 
in an Orange Empire Conference basketball game at Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago led, 55-34, with 15:45 to play, but Saddleback rallied to pull 
within 68-66 on a reverse layup by Matt Thompson. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago moved ahead, 70-66, on two free throws by Matt Lein, then 
Hunter went to work. He had a steal and later made two free throws to put the 
Dons ahead, 72-66, with 2:59 left. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback then came downcourt but Hunter intercepted a pass again. He later 
got the ball on the baseline, made a short jumper and was fouled. He made the 
free throw and Rancho Santiago led, 75-66, with 2:03 left. 
</P>
<P>
Hunter, who is normally first off the bench, started Saturday for Corie Blount, 
who has been ill the past week. Hunter finished with 14 points for Rancho 
Santiago (24-2, 7-1). 
</P>
<P>
Gene Altamirano led the Dons with 21 points and Matt Lien and Alvin Loftis each 
had 17. 
</P>
<P>
Charles Lockard scored 22 of his game-high 26 in the second half for Saddleback 
(8-17, 1-8), Thompson added 20 and Terrell Malone 10. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago trails first-place Cypress, which maintained its lead Saturday 
with an 80-54 victory over Fullerton, by 1 1/2 games. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
